<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1. Alendar line.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Bulwark of Alendar (63)<br>
Effect: Unknown #162 (100/20/1600)<br>
Cost: 300 + peridot<br>
Skill: Abjuration<br>
Cast/Recast: 2sec/15sec<br>
Target: Single<br>
Duration: 36 min.<br>
Message: A bright blue aura surrounds you.<br>
<br>
Other spells of this line:<br>
Protection of Alendar (55) (100/20/1200, peridot)<br>
Guard of Alendar (44) (100/20/700, jasper)<br>
Ward of Alendar (29) (100/20/460, bloodstone)<br>
<br>
Some sort of protection spell, apparently.  Not sure what 100/20 are, but the last number seems to do with hitpoints.   No idea what this is, but fairly sure this is not a rune equivalent - lvl 34 Rune III takes jasper and gives ~230hp protection.   A lvl 29 spell giving 460 for a bloodstone would obsolete the Rune line.  Also, clerics get a near identical 'Vie' series:  lvl 63 Bulwark of Vie is 'Unknown #162(100/10/1600)'<br>
<br>
Guessing as to what effect might be:<br>
DOT damage rune?   I know that current Rune series does not protect one vs. DOT spells.  This might.<br>
Spell damage only rune?  Won't protect vs. melee.<br>
Death safeguard?  Unlike Rune that provides damage barrier that must be broken before player starts taking damage,   Imagine a Rune that kicks in when a player is knocked unconscious.<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>2. Reflect line</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Reflect (58, NEC/WIZ/MAG/ENC)<br>
Effect: Unknown #158(100/50/50)<br>
Cost:150<br>
Skill: Abjuration<br>
Cast/Recast:  1.5sec/2min<br>
Target: Self<br>
Duration: 2 ticks (12 sec)<br>
Message:  A reflective aura surrounds you.<br>
<br>
Other spells of this line:<br>
Bounce (44) (100/40/40)<br>
<br>
We have a self-only, very fast-casting, short duration protective spell, but with a longish recast.   Available to all int caster classes.  <br>
Apparently, this spell will reflect back some type of damage for 12 seconds.   Question is, what type?   Melee?  Magic?  Both?   Full reflect or only a certain portion?  <br>
<br>
-------------------------------------------<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>3.  Deception</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Deception: (63)<br>
Effect: Unknown #156 (100/1/0)<br>
Cost: 200 + peridot<br>
Skill: Divination<br>
Cast/Recast: 6sec/2.5sec<br>
Target: Self<br>
Duration: 36min<br>
Message: Your form changes.<br>
<br>
Ok, this is apparently an Illusion.   But what does it change you to?   Guess:  takes either nearest mob, or random mob in zone, and make enchanter look like it.  <br>
<br>
------------------------------------------<br>
There is also Ordinance spell (52), which seems exact equivalent of Dictate, but lower level.<br>
<br>
What are your thoughts, people? <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bregalad Alcarin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, High Elf Phantasmist, Xev &lt;Legends of Westwood&gt;<br>
